Subject Re Albert Sabin From James Lippard In article John King writes Discussion on Josephus inserts Am I correct then in assuming that that Josephus did in fact write about Jesus but Christian copists embellished it Jack That is indeed the present Contrary to what Fox has been saying however present consensus is not that the longer passage in Josephus about Jesus was inserted but only that it was There is no question that it was at least modified based on what Origen says that Josephus did not recognize Jesus as the Messiah but I don't think the argument that it appears out of context is a very good I haven't looked at the context for a while perhaps somebody could give some of the sentences which precede and follow the Jesus Jim Lippard Lippard of Philosophy Lippard University of Arizona Tucson AZ